01:16:16.361 --> 01:16:20.321
And then the cool thing about publishing the source files,

01:16:20.321 --> 01:16:22.002
we'll discard those changes,

01:16:22.002 --> 01:16:24.922
is it now has all the code it needs to rebuild this

01:16:24.922 --> 01:16:26.441
whenever I want it to.

01:16:26.441 --> 01:16:29.241
And so I could ask it to rebuild this dashboard

01:16:29.241 --> 01:16:30.801
on a schedule,

01:16:30.801 --> 01:16:34.721
which makes sense if my code is reading in a data source

01:16:34.721 --> 01:16:37.002
and it gets updated from time to time.

01:16:37.002 --> 01:16:37.881
So for example,

01:16:37.881 --> 01:16:42.881
I could ask Connect to maybe every week

01:16:43.562 --> 01:16:46.081
on Monday or maybe Sunday night,

01:16:46.081 --> 01:16:47.241
I don't know,

01:16:47.241 --> 01:16:48.922
to rebuild this.

01:16:48.922 --> 01:16:51.801
And then it will collect the most recent version

01:16:51.801 --> 01:16:53.601
of that data file when it rebuilds it.

01:16:53.601 --> 01:16:55.642
And so when people come in Monday morning,

01:16:55.642 --> 01:16:56.482
all that week,

01:16:56.482 --> 01:16:59.202
they'll be seeing the most updated data for that week.

01:16:59.202 --> 01:17:01.321
And the next week it'll update again.

