01:22:03.322 --> 01:22:05.721
There's two parts of this file

01:22:05.721 --> 01:22:10.481
where we will be adding stuff or expecting AI to add stuff.

01:22:10.481 --> 01:22:13.642
And that is here in this UI object.

01:22:13.642 --> 01:22:15.041
This is where you put the things

01:22:15.041 --> 01:22:16.721
that will appear in your app.

01:22:17.601 --> 01:22:22.601
So that's where you'll put your inputs and your outputs.

01:22:23.962 --> 01:22:24.962
And then down below,

01:22:24.962 --> 01:22:27.122
this is where you'll tell the server computer

01:22:27.122 --> 01:22:30.122
how to build those outputs from the inputs.

01:22:30.122 --> 01:22:32.522
And I like to think of it with a restaurant analogy

01:22:32.522 --> 01:22:34.202
up top this UI part,

01:22:34.202 --> 01:22:36.401
that's like where you create a restaurant

01:22:36.401 --> 01:22:38.962
for people to come in and order things off a menu

01:22:38.962 --> 01:22:40.721
to also put there for them.

01:22:40.721 --> 01:22:41.562
Then down below,

01:22:41.562 --> 01:22:42.882
this is like where you write the cookbook

01:22:42.882 --> 01:22:44.082
to give to the kitchen staff.

01:22:44.082 --> 01:22:46.682
So when someone orders something off the menu,

01:22:47.481 --> 01:22:48.721
they could look up how to make it.

01:22:52.002 --> 01:22:54.122
So there's your crash course on Shiny.

